snippet: Jessie Baskin, 22, a former band member charged in the death of a Florida A&M drum major, on Wednesday pleaded no contest to manslaughter and could go to prison in the beating.
abstract: Jessie Baskin, former band member charged in the hazing death of Florida A&M drum major Robert Champion, pleads no contest to manslaughter, and could become the first person to go to prison in the beating.
lead_paragraph: Jessie Baskin, 22, a former band member charged in the death of a Florida A&M drum major, on Wednesday pleaded no contest to manslaughter and could go to prison in the beating.

headline.main: Florida: Ex-Band Member Agrees to Plea in Hazing Death
headline.print_headline: Florida: Manslaughter Plea In Hazing of Band Member
